  "title": "Recruitment Consutlant",
  "description": "<p><strong>🟦Working location: Ang Mo Kio</strong></p><p><strong>🟦5 days work week</strong></p><p><strong>🟦Possess CEI Certificate will be an advantage </strong></p><p><strong>🟦Basic: up to $3,500</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage <strong>end-to-end (360) recruitment</strong>, covering business development, client servicing, and candidate placement.</p></li><li><p>Identify and develop new business opportunities through outreach, networking, and referrals.</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong relationships with clients to understand hiring needs and workforce requirements.</p></li><li><p>Source, screen, and interview candidates for assigned roles.</p></li><li><p>Match candidates to suitable job opportunities and manage the interview process.</p></li><li><p>Negotiate job offers, fees, and placement terms with clients and candidates.<br /></p><p></p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree holders welcome</p></li><li><p>1–3 years of experience in 360 recruitment, preferably in a recruitment agency environment.</p></li><li><p>Good communication and negotiation skills</p></li><li><p>Target-driven, resilient, and motivated by performance incentives<br /></p><p></p></li></ul><p>EA License No: 19C9611</p><p>EA Personnel Reg No: R1433735 Teng Wei Mun (Celest)</p>",
